**Theorem A.1**.: _Gradient of the loss \(\mathcal{L}(\bm{\lambda})\) with respect to the expectation parameter \(\bm{\lambda}\), i.e., \(\nabla_{\bm{\lambda}}\mathcal{L}(\bm{\lambda})\), is equal to the natural gradient with respect to natural parameter \(\bm{\phi}\), i.e., \(\bm{F}^{-1}\nabla_{\bm{\phi}}\mathcal{L}(\bm{\phi})\). This can be expressed as the following:_

\[\nabla_{\bm{\lambda}}\mathcal{L}(\bm{\lambda})=\bm{F}^{-1}\nabla_{\bm{\phi}} \mathcal{L}(\bm{\phi})\] (19)

